cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with machine learning and rule-extraction techniques for highly accurate prediction models, which are often difficult to interpret. The paper focuses on the challenges of rule-extraction in the context of ultra-high-dimensional and sparse data, which is a common problem in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The data used in the study is behavioral and textual, which falls under the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between explainability, fidelity, accuracy, and stability, which are important considerations in the field of cryptography (cs.CR).
